# PokeManiac Kotlin & Android Coding Standards

> **Guiding principle:** Standards exist to solve real problems, not to be followed for their own sake. Don't apply a pattern just because it's "best practice" if it makes the code harder to understand. Code must remain readable by a senior Android developer who doesn't know this codebase. See `pokemaniac-guide.mdc` for the full engineering philosophy.

## Immutability First

### Collections
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD - mutable
val items: MutableList<Item> = mutableListOf()

// ✅ GOOD - immutable in public APIs
val items: PersistentList<Item> = persistentListOf()

// ✅ GOOD - Flow returns immutable
fun getItems(): Flow<List<Item>>
```

### Data Classes
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD - var properties
data class UserUI(var id: String, var name: String)

// ✅ GOOD - val properties
data class UserUI(val id: String, val name: String)
```

### StateFlow
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD - expose mutable
val state: MutableStateFlow<UiState>

// ✅ GOOD - expose immutable
private val _state = MutableStateFlow<UiState>()
val state: StateFlow<UiState> = _state.asStateFlow()
```

