## Object Expressions & Lambdas

### Use Trailing Lambda Syntax
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - trailing lambda
items.map { item ->
    item.name
}

button.setOnClickListener {
    handleClick()
}

// ❌ BAD - not trailing
items.map(fun(item) { return item.name })
```

### Destructuring
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - destructuring in lambdas
data class Point(val x: Int, val y: Int)

points.forEach { (x, y) ->
    println("x: $x, y: $y")
}

// ✅ GOOD - destructuring in for
for ((key, value) in map) {
    println("$key -> $value")
}
```

---

## Scope Functions

### Choose Right Scope Function
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD - apply for object configuration
user.apply {
    name = "John"
    email = "john@example.com"
}

// ✅ GOOD - also for builder pattern
val person = Person().apply {
    firstName = "John"
    lastName = "Doe"
}

// ✅ GOOD - let for safe call chaining
user?.let { u ->
    updateProfile(u)
}

// ✅ GOOD - with for multiple operations
with(user) {
    println(name)
    println(email)
}

// ❌ BAD - mixing scope functions
user.apply { name = "John" }.let { u -> process(u) }
```

